article.headline: Northeastern 73, Detroit 68
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Jose Juan Barea scored 27 points and Shawn James added 12 points and six blocked shots to lead Northeastern past Detroit 73-68 on Wednesday night. Northeastern (3-4) saw an early 19-point lead dwindle to just two by the opening minutes of the second half, but the Huskies pulled ahead for good with a 15-3 run. Barea engineered the run with seven points and a pair of assists as Northeastern jumped back on top, 49-35. Jon Goode and Chuck Bailey each scored 17 points for Detroit. The Titans (1-5) have lost five straight and are off to their worst start since 1988-1989, when they began the season 1-12. Detroit was hampered by 23 turnovers. After losing to Connecticut by 37 points Monday, Northeastern opened the game with three new starters -- James, Adrian Martinez and Bobby Kelly. The shake-up paid off early as Northeastern raced out to leads of 17-2 and 29-10. But Detroit rallied with a 22-5 run, aided by a 22-9 first-half rebounding advantage, cutting Northeastern's lead to 34-32 with 18:18 left.
